The "Mini-Player" Logic
The Trigger: A button in the Title Bar or Player Bar (e.g., a "Picture-in-Picture" icon).

The Transformation:

Save the current window size (e.g., 1100x700).

Hide sidebar_frame and main_view_frame.

Shrink window to 600x100.

Turn on attributes('-topmost', True).

The Restoration:

Unhide the frames.

Restore original size.

Turn off "Always on Top".

The Prompt to Build It
Copy and paste this:

"I need to implement a 'Focus Mode' (Mini-Player). Please modify suno_layout.py.

1. Add the Toggle Button:

Add a small ctk.CTkButton to the Player Bar (bottom right, next to volume).

Use a 'Picture-in-Picture' icon (or text '⤢').

Command: self.toggle_mini_mode.

2. Implement toggle_mini_mode:

Create a state variable self.is_mini_mode = False.

If entering Mini Mode:

Save self.last_geometry = self.geometry().

Call self.sidebar_frame.grid_remove() to hide the sidebar.

Call self.pages_frame.grid_remove() (or whatever holds the tabs) to hide the library/downloader.

Resize the window: self.geometry("600x120").

Set self.attributes("-topmost", True) to keep it floating above other apps.

Change the toggle button icon/text to 'Expand' (⤡).

3. If exiting Mini Mode:

Call .grid() on the sidebar and pages frame to show them again.

Restore self.geometry(self.last_geometry).

Set self.attributes("-topmost", False).

Reset the button icon.

4. Window Behavior:

Ensure the window is resizable in Mini Mode so I can stretch it if needed."

